comments.body:
FYI, I think this might be necessary for some use cases. For example, I have Airflow extract data from dozens of APIs in parallel and write to the same target partitioned dataset (partitioned based on the Airflow scheduled date, so all files belong in the same batch folder) - this causes the part-0.parquet file to be overwritten each time which results in lost data instead of there being dozens of files.

For the meantime, I added the code below. I need to keep the \{i} it seems or I get an error:
{code:python}
            if self.create_uuid_filename:
                basename_template = guid() + "-{i}.parquet"
            else:
                basename_template = "part-{i}.parquet"
{code}
guid() is imported from pyarrow.utils
